---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import Aside from '../../../components/Aside.astro';
import {cacheSidebar} from '../../../data/cache-sidebar';
import {Code} from 'astro:components';
---

<DocsLayout title="Cache" sidebar={cacheSidebar}
            description="Coroutine-based in-memory caching for Kotlin Multiplatform" hilbert>

    <h1>Cache</h1>

    <p class="text-xl text-gray-400 !mt-2 !mb-8">
        A coroutine-based in-memory cache with pluggable eviction policies.
        Thread-safe, multiplatform, and allocation-aware.
    </p>

    <h2>Why a custom cache?</h2>

    <p>Most JVM caches (Caffeine, Guava) are excellent but JVM-only. When you need the same caching API in
        <code>commonMain</code> for code shared between JVM and JS, your options narrow quickly. Cache fills that gap
        with a clean builder API and pluggable behaviors that work on all Kotlin platforms.</p>

    <Aside>We needed caching in Slumber's serialization hot path. It had to be fast, multiplatform, and not pull
        in a JVM-only dependency. So here we are.
    </Aside>

    <h2>The core idea: pluggable behaviors, async eviction</h2>

    <p>Instead of one cache with many configuration flags, Cache uses composable <strong>behaviors</strong>. Stack them
        to get exactly the eviction policy you need.</p>

    <p>Eviction runs asynchronously in a Kotlin coroutine background loop — reading and writing the cache is
        fast because the calling thread never pays for eviction work. The loop integrates naturally with
        structured concurrency: cancel the coroutine scope and the evictor stops cleanly.</p>

    <Code code={`import io.peekandpoke.ultra.cache.fastCache
import kotlin.time.Duration.Companion.minutes
import kotlin.time.Duration.Companion.seconds

val cache = fastCache<String, UserProfile> {
    expireAfterAccess(5.minutes)
    maxEntries(1000)
}`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <h2>What you get</h2>

    <div class="not-prose grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-8">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02]">
            <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-1">TTL Expiration</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Expire entries after a configurable idle time. Resets on every access.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02]">
            <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-1">Max Entries</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">LRU eviction when the entry count exceeds a limit.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02]">
            <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-1">Max Memory</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Evict based on estimated object size. LRU when memory budget is
                exceeded.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02]">
            <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-1">Thread-Safe</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">All operations are synchronized. Safe for concurrent access from multiple
                coroutines.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02]">
            <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-1">Kotlin Multiplatform</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Works in <code>commonMain</code>, <code>jvmMain</code>, and
                <code>jsMain</code>.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02]">
            <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-1">Coroutine-Based</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Background processing loop for eviction. Cleans up automatically via
                WeakReference.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Quick taste</h2>

    <Code code={`import io.peekandpoke.ultra.cache.fastCache
import kotlin.time.Duration.Companion.minutes

val cache = fastCache<String, String> {
    expireAfterAccess(10.minutes)
    maxEntries(500)
}

// Put and get
cache.put("key", "value")
println(cache.get("key"))  // "value"

// Get-or-put pattern
val result = cache.getOrPut("user:42") {
    fetchUserFromDatabase("42")  // only called on cache miss
}

// Check and remove
println(cache.has("key"))    // true
cache.remove("key")
println(cache.has("key"))    // false

// Inspect
println(cache.size)          // number of entries
println(cache.keys)          // current key set`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <div class="not-prose mt-8">
        <a href="/ultra/cache/getting-started"
           class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-brand-600 text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-brand-500 transition-colors">
            Get started &rarr;
        </a>
    </div>

</DocsLayout>
